
[1]putty

   PUT'TY, n. A kind of paste or cement compounded of whiting and linseed
   oil, beaten or kneaded to the consistence of dough; used in fastening
   glass in sashes and in stopping crevices.

   1. A powder of calcined tin, used in polishing glass and steel.
